  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GameObject
    A general interface that defines what each object in the game should have.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Chap
    The main character of the game.
    Collectable
    Items that can be collected by the player in the game.
    Door
    A door that can only be unlocked with a key that has a certain color.
    Enemy
    The enemy in the game.
    Exit
    The maze's exit.
    ExitLock
    A lock to the maze's exit that can only be unlocked if the player has collected all the treasures.
    FreeTile
    An empty tile that the player can move to.
    InfoTile
    A tile that gives the player a hint on what to do so they can pass the current level.
    Inventory
    The inventory containing items that the player has.
    Key
    Class for collectable key in game.
    Level
    Levels for the game.
    Location
    This class is responsible for handling the location of each object in the maze.
    Maze
    Maze for each level.
    Tile
    An abstract class for different types of tiles.
    Treasure
    Treasures to be collected by the player.
    Wall
    A wall on the maze.
